This paper is likely to belong to the cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) sub-category as it focuses on the implementation of a fixed-point DNN system using FPGA hardware. The paper also employs training-based fixed-point weight optimization, which is a technique commonly used in hardware optimization. 

The cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category is also likely as the paper deals with DNNs and their implementation. 

The cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category is another possibility as the paper tests the implementation on the MNIST handwritten digit recognition benchmark, which is a common computer vision task. 

The cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category is also possible as the paper deals with DNNs and their implementation, which is a common topic in machine learning research. 

Finally, the cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) sub-category is a possibility as FPGA-based hardware implementation is an emerging technology in the field of deep learning and machine learning.
